description:
Check if an operation can be paginated.

	: type operation_name: string
	: param operation_name: The operation name.  This is the same name as the method name on the client.  For example, if the method name is create_foo, and you'd normally invoke the operation as client.create_foo( ** kwargs), if the create_foo operation can be paginated, you can use the call client.get_paginator('create_foo').
